==English==

===Etymology===
From Japanese shōgun ([[将軍]]), from an abbreviation of Seii Taishogun ([[征夷大将軍]]) which means the general who overcomes the barbarians.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|shō'gŭn}}, {{IPA|/ˈʃəʊɡʌn/}}, {{SAMPA|/"S@UgVn/}}
* {{rhymes|əʊɡən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The supreme [[generalissimo]] of feudal [[Japan]].

